JOS – Plateau State Deputy Governor and frontline governorship aspirant at the 2023 gubernatorial race in the state, Professor Sonni Tyoden, has facilitated with the Muslim Ummah in the state and the country at large on the successful completion of this year’s Ramadan fast. A statement by his media campaign office which was made available to SATURDAY INDEPENDENT stated that the Deputy Governor expressed “gratitude to the Almighty Allah for giving the Muslim Ummah the strength and endurance to go through the spiritual obligation at this trying moment.” He said further: “It is heartwarming, encouraging and fulfilling that throughout the one month, the Muslim Ummah particularly those of plateau demonstrated a lot of resilience and determination in complying with one of the tenets of Islam.” Tyoden enjoined the Muslim Ummah to demonstrate all the virtues of the Ramadan as enshrined in the Hadith and the Holy Quran. He further admonished the Muslims to continue to show compassion, love and respect to one another for peaceful coexistence in the state. The governorship aspirant urged them to pray for the country to surmount its challenges. Tyoden reassured them that no challenges are unsurmountable with the support and prayers of all and sundry. The Deputy Governor called on people of other faiths to pray for the peaceful and successful conduct of the forthcoming election in the country.